fuzz had Thunder Road staked out...

650
00:42:54.623 --> 00:42:56.682
and everybody got hauled
to the clink.

651
00:42:58.660 --> 00:43:00.321
Nobody's gonna catch
Greased Lightnin'.

652
00:43:00.429 --> 00:43:02.624
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

653
00:43:03.732 --> 00:43:06.963
- Somebody snakin' you. Danny?
- Oh. bite the weenie. Rizz.

654
00:43:07.069 --> 00:43:08.559
With relish.

655
00:43:13.608 --> 00:43:17.510
- I don't know about these chicks.
- They're only good for one thing.

656
00:43:17.579 --> 00:43:19.513
Then what are you supposed
to do with them...

657
00:43:19.581 --> 00:43:22.106
for the other 23 hours
and 45 minutes of the day?

658
00:43:22.384 --> 00:43:24.784
Is that all it takes.
1 5 minutes?

659
00:43:27.589 --> 00:43:29.784
Want some new music?

660
00:43:29.891 --> 00:43:31.119
Yeah.

661
00:43:31.393 --> 00:43:33.122
I need some money.

662
00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:37.555
Thanks.

663
00:43:43.672 --> 00:43:45.572
I'll be right back.

664
00:43:50.879 --> 00:43:51.777
Hi. Danny.

665
00:43:53.882 --> 00:43:56.476
- I can't talk to you right now.
- What are you doing later?

666
00:43:56.585 --> 00:43:59.349
- I can't talk. all right?
- Call me.

667
00:44:10.098 --> 00:44:12.066
- Hi. Sandy.
- Oh. hi.

668
00:44:12.200 --> 00:44:14.464
- How are you?
- Fine. thanks.

669
00:44:14.603 --> 00:44:16.127
Well. that's good.

670
00:44:16.438 --> 00:44:19.635
Hey. Sandy. I've been wantin'
to talk to you for a long time.

671
00:44:19.741 --> 00:44:20.969
What about?

672
00:44:21.076 --> 00:44:25.137
About that night at the bonfire.
The way I acted. that was terrible.

673
00:44:25.414 --> 00:44:27.882
I mean. it really was.
It wasn't me. You gotta know that.

674
00:44:27.983 --> 00:44:31.680
It was me. of course.
But it wasn't me.

675
00:44:31.787 --> 00:44:33.049
And I--

676
00:44:33.121 --> 00:44:35.555
Sandy. I got
this image. right?

677
00:44:35.624 --> 00:44:43.832
That's why I'm so glad
that Tom's such a simple person.

678
00:44:43.832 --> 00:44:47.996
Simple's right. Too bad
his brains are in his biceps.

679
00:44:48.103 --> 00:44:50.731
Jealous. are you?

680
00:44:50.806 --> 00:44:54.173
Jealous? Oh. come on. Sandy.
Don't make me laugh.

681
00:44:55.477 --> 00:44:57.411
What have you ever done?

682
00:45:00.148 --> 00:45:04.414
Oh. Oh. come on. I can run
circles around those jerks.

683
00:45:04.553 --> 00:45:06.214
I'll believe that
when I see it.

684
00:45:30.512 --> 00:45:33.743
Let's start with the first rule--
cutting down to two packs a day.

685
00:45:33.882 --> 00:45:34.849
Here we go.

686
00:45:38.753 --> 00:45:41.085
What sort of athletics
are you interested in?

687
00:45:42.190 --> 00:45:45.057
- Do you like the rings?
- Yeah. I installed some rings...

688
00:45:45.160 --> 00:45:47.685
just a couple of weeks ago.

689
00:45:49.631 --> 00:45:52.759
Well. the first thing we have
to do is. you have to change.

690
00:45:52.868 --> 00:45:54.961
I know. That's why I'm here--
to change.

691
00:45:55.070 --> 00:45:56.970
No. your clothes.

692
00:46:05.180 --> 00:46:07.114
Let's knock it off.
Fellas...

693
00:46:08.316 --> 00:46:11.285
I wanna introduce
a new man-- Danny.

694
00:46:11.586 --> 00:46:13.486
Let's give him a tryout.

695
00:46:14.990 --> 00:46:18.050
- You better watch it.
- Come on. come on.

696
00:46:18.159 --> 00:46:20.627
- A little fire. Here we go.
- Come on! Come on!

697
00:46:20.729 --> 00:46:21.855
Watch it.

698
00:46:33.008 --> 00:46:34.134
You have to dribble.

699
00:46:38.680 --> 00:46:40.773
- Here you go. Coach.
- Thank you. son.

700
00:46:40.916 --> 00:46:43.749
Just dribble the ball. put it in
the basket. Think you can do that?

701
00:46:43.852 --> 00:46:45.945
Can I do that?

702
00:46:46.054 --> 00:46:48.887
- Okay. let's go.
- Danny. over here.

703
00:46:48.957 --> 00:46:50.982
Let's go.

704
00:46:51.092 --> 00:46:53.788
- Come on. Arnold.
- Get it up.

705
00:46:53.895 --> 00:46:55.294
That's good.

706
00:46:55.564 --> 00:46:58.328
- Get him. Danny.
- Here we are. Go. go!

707
00:46:58.600 --> 00:47:00.534
Get him.
That's it. That's it.

708
00:47:03.171 --> 00:47:05.639
- What did I do?
- Is he kidding?

709
00:47:10.145 --> 00:47:12.579
I want you to meet
your wrestling partner.

710
00:47:12.647 --> 00:47:14.808
Danny. Andy.

711
00:47:16.651 --> 00:47:19.313
- Are you crazy?
- Come on. come on.

712
00:47:19.588 --> 00:47:21.954
Come on. Let's start.
Get in the first position.

713
00:47:22.023 --> 00:47:24.548
Danny. you get down.

714
00:47:24.659 --> 00:47:26.786
Okay. Andy. get on.
Ready?

715
00:47:31.666 --> 00:47:34.601
Hold it. Hold it.
Come on.

716
00:47:34.669 --> 00:47:38.332
Danny. you gotta try.
Try. Come on.

717
00:47:38.607 --> 00:47:41.735
All right. Andy. let's change
positions. You get down. Come on.

718
00:47:47.816 --> 00:47:49.716
All right. Ready?

719
00:47:52.854 --> 00:47:54.651
- Give?
- Yeah. I give.

720
00:47:54.756 --> 00:47:56.155
Good.

721
00:48:01.229 --> 00:48:02.161
He's a hitter.

722
00:48:05.867 --> 00:48:09.803
You're gonna like baseball.
It's not much of a contact sport.

723
00:48:09.904 --> 00:48:12.338
Get in there
and see what you can do.

724
00:48:12.440 --> 00:48:15.773
- Throw the ball. Let's play.
- Where would you like it?

725
00:48:15.877 --> 00:48:17.811
Let's pitch this guy
out of here.

726
00:48:17.912 --> 00:48:20.403
This boy can't even bat.
Can't even hold--

727
00:48:20.682 --> 00:48:23.810
- Strike!
- I told you. He doesn't even swing.

728
00:48:23.918 --> 00:48:26.716
What kind of ballplayer are you?
Put it in here. pitcher.

729
00:48:29.190 --> 00:48:30.680
Strike!

730
00:48:32.160 --> 00:48:36.028
A little pepper. A little fire.
Let's see you hit it.

731
00:48:36.131 --> 00:48:38.224
Put it in. Put it in.

732
00:48:40.135 --> 00:48:41.898
Foul ball!

733
00:48:44.406 --> 00:48:47.102
- Easy. easy. easy. easy.
- Come on.

734
00:48:47.208 --> 00:48:49.699
Put the bat down.
Put the bat down.

735
00:48:51.012 --> 00:48:54.675
There's a lot of other sports
that don't have any contact at all.

736
00:48:54.816 --> 00:48:57.751
- Oh. yeah? Like what?
- Like track.

737
00:48:57.852 --> 00:49:00.787
- What do you mean. running?
- It ain't just like running.

738
00:49:02.023 --> 00:49:05.823
It's something that needs endurance.
something that needs stamina...

739
00:49:05.927 --> 00:49:09.226
Iike long-distance running...

740
00:49:09.297 --> 00:49:11.731
cross-country running.

741
00:49:13.935 --> 00:49:17.336
- That could be cool.
- Good.

742
00:49:18.907 --> 00:49:21.273
Come on.
Keep those legs high!

743
00:49:49.304 --> 00:49:51.204
Are you all right?

744
00:49:52.741 --> 00:49:54.470
Danny. talk to me.

745
00:49:56.044 --> 00:49:59.070
The least you can do is talk to me
after the way you treated me.

746
00:49:59.180 --> 00:50:01.910
The way I treated--
I told you I was sorry about that.

747
00:50:02.050 --> 00:50:03.950
I got you talking.

748
00:50:05.487 --> 00:50:07.955
- You sure you're okay?
- Yes. I'm fine.

749
00:50:09.824 --> 00:50:11.724
You're still going out
with that jockstrap?

750
00:50:11.826 --> 00:50:14.056
Well--

751
00:50:14.162 --> 00:50:16.756
Well. is he taking you
to the dance?

752
00:50:16.865 --> 00:50:18.799
- That all depends.
- On what?

753
00:50:18.867 --> 00:50:20.357
- On you.
- On me?

754
00:50:20.468 --> 00:50:23.494
- Yeah.
- He can stag it.

755
00:50:29.144 --> 00:50:31.078
Come on.

756
00:50:42.290 --> 00:50:45.191
Sandy. come on.
Let's go someplace else.

757
00:50:45.293 --> 00:50:47.557
Why?

758
00:50:47.829 --> 00:50:50.297
Because we can't
be alone here. that's why.

759
00:50:56.905 --> 00:50:59.135
Two burgers
and a moo juice coming up.

760
00:51:03.178 --> 00:51:05.078
You nearly pulled
my arm out of the socket.

761
00:51:05.213 --> 00:51:07.579
I didn't wanna miss this table.
It's the best table they got.

762
00:51:09.384 --> 00:51:12.376
- What are you doing?
- I just want a little privacy.

763
00:51:12.487 --> 00:51:16.981
- What'll it be. kids?
- Cherry soda. please.

764
00:51:17.091 --> 00:51:20.549
I'm not very hungry.Just give me
a double burger with everything...

765
00:51:20.829 --> 00:51:22.888
and a cherry soda
with chocolate ice cream.

766
00:51:22.997 --> 00:51:24.897
That sounds good.
I'll have the same.

767
00:51:24.999 --> 00:51:27.160
The same?
You can eat a lot.

768
00:51:27.268 --> 00:51:29.964
- You're funny.
- No. I'm not. You are.

769
00:51:30.071 --> 00:51:34.201
- How you doin'. Zuk?
- Hi. Rizzo. How are you?

770
00:51:34.275 --> 00:51:36.209
Peachy keen. jellybean.

771
00:51:37.512 --> 00:51:40.003
You got a couple of quarters?
We can split an Eskimo Pie.

772
00:51:40.114 --> 00:51:42.082
My dutch-treat days
are over.

773
00:51:42.183 --> 00:51:44.378
You plan
on staying home a lot.

774
00:51:44.452 --> 00:51:47.250
Greetings. pals and gals.

775
00:51:47.355 --> 00:51:50.586
I got 23 cents. Anybody wanna
chip in for a Dogsled Delight?

776
00:51:50.859 --> 00:51:53.157
I don't know
where all my money goes.

777
00:51:53.261 --> 00:51:55.354
A dime here.
1 5 cents there.

778
00:51:55.463 --> 00:51:58.523
Another couple of months. Frenchie
will be able to take us all out.

779
00:51:58.633 --> 00:52:00.533
- A working girl with income.
- That's right.

780
00:52:00.635 --> 00:52:03.570
They don't pay you very much
to start off with.

781
00:52:03.671 --> 00:52:05.901
That's still more than we make.
so ante up...

782
00:52:06.007 --> 00:52:07.941
because I don't get
my allowance until Friday.

783
00:52:08.009 --> 00:52:10.034
- You get an allowance?
- When I'm a good boy. I do.

784
00:52:10.144 --> 00:52:12.874
Viola. a Dogsled Delight
with four spoons!

785
00:52:12.981 --> 00:52:15.279
- And an Eskimo Pie with a knife.
- Hiya. gang!

786
00:52:15.350 --> 00:52:17.978
Hi.Jan. Hi. Putz.

787
00:52:18.119 --> 00:52:21.055
Here you are.
Grab it and growl.

788
00:52:21.055 --> 00:52:21.077
Here you are.
Grab it and growl.

789
00:52:23.958 --> 00:52:26.085
I got so many hickeys.
people will think I'm a leper.

790
00:52:26.194 --> 00:52:30.255
Cheer up. A hickey from Kenickie
is like a Hallmark card.

791
00:52:30.331 --> 00:52:32.526
"When you care enough
to send the very best."

792
00:52:34.269 --> 00:52:35.236
You pig.

793
00:52:35.370 --> 00:52:37.497
I love it
when you talk dirty.

794
00:52:39.140 --> 00:52:42.041
My parents want to invite you
for tea on Sunday. Want to come?

795
00:52:44.078 --> 00:52:46.979
- I don't like tea.
- You don't have to drink tea.

796
00:52:48.149 --> 00:52:50.049
Well. I don't like parents.

797
00:52:52.654 --> 00:52:55.054
Want some?

798
00:52:55.156 --> 00:52:57.124
You sure
are a cheap date.

799
00:52:57.225 --> 00:52:59.159
I didn't mean it
the way it came out.

800
00:52:59.227 --> 00:53:00.159
I understand.

801
00:53:00.228 --> 00:53:02.162
I always thought you were
a very understanding person.

802
00:53:02.263 --> 00:53:03.662
I am.

803
00:53:03.932 --> 00:53:08.096
And I also think that there's
more to you than just fat.

804
00:53:08.202 --> 00:53:09.567
Thanks.

805
00:53:09.671 --> 00:53:12.606
You're welcome.
You got a date for the dance-off?

806
00:53:12.707 --> 00:53:14.265
- You wanna go?
- Yeah.

807
00:53:14.375 --> 00:53:18.709
I'll be a senior forever. I have to
study for that dumb algebra test.

808
00:53:18.980 --> 00:53:21.676
You're in luck. luscious.
You got an armed escort home.

809
00:53:21.749 --> 00:53:24.479
It's not the arms
I'm worried about. Sonny.

810
00:53:24.585 --> 00:53:26.314
It's the hands.

811
00:53:26.387 --> 00:53:28.514
She loves me.

812
00:53:30.425 --> 00:53:32.950
- You comin'. French?
- I don't think so.

813
00:53:33.061 --> 00:53:35.052
I think I'd like to hang out
a little bit longer.

814
00:53:35.163 --> 00:53:38.564
- All right.
- I have been dieting all day long.

815
00:53:38.666 --> 00:53:41.032
My mom's apple pie
is better than this stuff.

816
00:53:41.102 --> 00:53:43.332
- You want a piece?
- Yeah. sure.

817
00:53:44.539 --> 00:53:45.733
- Hey. Putzie.
- Yeah?

818
00:53:46.040 --> 00:53:47.598
Fifteen minutes.

819
00:53:48.977 --> 00:53:51.138
I'm kind of worried
about this dance-off.

820
00:53:51.245 --> 00:53:53.338
Maybe they dance differently
than we do back home.

821
00:53:53.414 --> 00:53:56.383
Don't worry about it. Maybe
we'll invent the kangaroo bop.

822
00:53:58.753 --> 00:54:00.618
Let's get
out of here. Sandy.

823
00:54:00.722 --> 00:54:03.213
Zuk. see you later.

824
00:54:03.291 --> 00:54:05.691
- Bye. Frenchie.
- See you. Sandy.

825
00:54:08.229 --> 00:54:11.198
Great. I get stuck with
the check again. Give me money.

826
00:54:12.433 --> 00:54:14.628
Okay. what is it?
What's with you tonight?

827
00:54:14.736 --> 00:54:16.636
You got the personality
of a wet mop.

828
00:54:16.738 --> 00:54:19.571
- Don't start with me.
- Sure. fine. Eureka.

829
00:54:19.640 --> 00:54:22.438
- How about I finish with you?
- Finish this!

830
00:54:24.545 --> 00:54:26.137
To you from me. Pinky Lee.

831
00:54:28.416 --> 00:54:29.747
Sorry. French.

832
00:54:35.523 --> 00:54:40.790
Rizzo. I wanna talk to you. now!

833
00:54:41.062 --> 00:54:43.257
No use crying
over spilled milk shake.

834
00:54:43.331 --> 00:54:45.265
Oh. I'll be okay.

835
00:54:46.834 --> 00:54:48.768
It's near closing time.

836
00:54:49.037 --> 00:54:51.267
Do you mind if I stay around
a little longer. Vi?

837
00:54:51.372 --> 00:54:53.306
No. Suit yourself.

838
00:54:53.408 --> 00:54:55.774
- Wow!
- What?

839
00:54:56.077 --> 00:54:59.410
Well. I hate to tell you this. but
your hair looks like an Easter egg.

840
00:55:00.314 --> 00:55:05.513
Oh. yeah. Well. I had a little
trouble in tinting class.

841
00:55:05.620 --> 00:55:09.249
In fact. I had a little trouble
in all my classes.

842
00:55:09.357 --> 00:55:11.621
Beauty school sure wasn't
what I thought it was gonna be.

843
00:55:11.692 --> 00:55:14.183
Oh. nothing ever is.

844
00:55:19.500 --> 00:55:22.162
I dropped out.

845
00:55:22.270 --> 00:55:24.397
What do you think
of waitressing?

846
00:55:24.539 --> 00:55:26.439
You're too young to know.

847
00:55:27.608 --> 00:55:30.133
Maybe I could be
a telephone operator.

848
00:55:31.379 --> 00:55:35.611
I don't think I would like to wear
those little things over my ears.

849
00:55:35.716 --> 00:55:39.379
God. if only I could have
a guardian angel...

850
00:55:39.487 --> 00:55:41.387
to tell me what to do...

851
00:55:41.489 --> 00:55:44.049
Iike Debbie Reynolds
had in Tammy.

852
00:55:44.158 --> 00:55:45.750
What do you think?

853
00:55:45.860 --> 00:55:48.328
If you find him.
give him my phone number.

854
00:56:04.445 --> 00:56:08.404
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Your story's sad to tell</i>

855
00:56:08.516 --> 00:56:13.078
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>A teenage ne'er-do-well</i>

856
00:56:13.187 --> 00:56:16.156
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Most mixed-up nondelinquent</i>

857
00:56:16.257 --> 00:56:18.817
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>On the block</i>

858
00:56:20.528 --> 00:56:25.397
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Your future's
so unclear now</i>

859
00:56:25.466 --> 00:56:29.562
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>What's left
of your career now</i>

860
00:56:29.670 --> 00:56:34.164
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Can't even get a trade-in</i>

861
00:56:34.275 --> 00:56:37.642
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>On your smock</i>

862
00:56:52.660 --> 00:56:54.685
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Beauty school dropout</i>

863
00:56:55.930 --> 00:56:59.297
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>No graduation day for you</i>

864
00:56:59.400 --> 00:57:01.300
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Beauty school dropout</i>

865
00:57:02.637 --> 00:57:05.765
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Missed your midterms
and flunked shampoo</i>

866
00:57:05.873 --> 00:57:09.331
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Well. at least you
could have taken time</i>

867
00:57:09.443 --> 00:57:12.344
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>To wash and clean
your clothes up</i>

868
00:57:12.446 --> 00:57:14.846
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>After spendin'
all that dough</i>

869
00:57:14.982 --> 00:57:18.247
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>To have the doctor
fix your nose up</i>

870
00:57:18.319 --> 00:57:21.516
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>- Baby. get movin'
- Baby. get movin'</i>

871
00:57:21.622 --> 00:57:24.750
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Why keep your
feeble hopes alive</i>

872
00:57:24.859 --> 00:57:27.919
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>- What are you proving
- What are you proving</i>

873
00:57:27.995 --> 00:57:31.590
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>You've got the dream
but not the drive</i>

874
00:57:31.666 --> 00:57:34.726
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>If you go for your diploma</i>

875
00:57:34.835 --> 00:57:37.531
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>You could join a steno pool</i>

876
00:57:37.672 --> 00:57:42.939
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Turn in your teasing comb
and go back to high school</i>

877
00:57:47.014 --> 00:57:50.211
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>- Beauty school dropout
- Beauty school dropout</i>

878
00:57:50.318 --> 00:57:53.219
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Hangin' around
the corner store</i>

879
00:57:53.321 --> 00:57:54.982
<font color="#FFFF99"><i>Beauty school dropout</i>

